## About This Workflow
All versions of **Qwen Image Edit for Urbanism** are designed as **fully local AI pipelines** â€” running offline, without APIs or cloud dependencies. While optimized for **urbanism and architectural visualization**, this workflow can be adapted to any image-editing or visual design context.  

## About v1.3

Version 1.3 introduces mask-based, localized editing, allowing Qwen to modify only the regions the user selects while preserving the rest of the image exactly as it is. Instead of using an Empty Latent (which regenerates the whole scene), this version switches to VAE Encode â†’ Set Latent Noise (masked), ensuring edits remain tightly confined to the mask.

A new Grow Mask utility expands and softens the painted mask, improving transitions and preventing harsh edges. The mask can be created directly in ComfyUI by right-clicking the base image and choosing Open in Mask Editor, and a built-in preview shows the final mask after expansion and blur.

Blocks 1 and 2 (single-image editing and sequential multi-image editing) remain unchanged; users simply activate the block they want by right-clicking the group and selecting Active or Bypass. Block 3 can also be combined with the sequential loader to apply the same masked edit across a batch of images.
